{
  "article_id": "Carl1952",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "["
      },
      {
        "text": "The editors",
        "entity_keys": [
          "sbh",
          "atay"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " will welcome as contributions to this section of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Western Folklore",
        "entity_key": "wfolk",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " small items of traditional materials and inquiries designed to elicit information about such materials. In general, discussion of the materials here offered will be brief. Records of facts likely to be lost or overlooked and inquiries which our readers may be able to answer will be the typical items.]"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "[...]"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Off the coast of ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " stands ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", once populated by ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a tribe of peaceful seagoing Indians",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". So peaceful, in fact, that history recounts it led to their downfall and ultimate virtual extinction years before American pioneers fought their way through other Indian tribes in order to reach ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_local",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Because of constant raids by "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Russian[s] and Aleuts",
        "entity_keys": [
          "rfurcompany",
          "iba",
          "natam_aleuts"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", these "
      },
      {
        "text": "island Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " were rescued back in 1835 by the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Spanish padres",
        "entity_key": "misfats",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "mainland missions",
        "entity_key": "mi_mainlandmissions",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "and from this results the strange tale of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the lost woman of San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "When ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the rescue ship",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " was about to sail, ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "one of the women",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " jumped overboard crying that ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " had been left behind.",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " Then, according to legend, a sudden storm drove "
      },
      {
        "text": "the ship",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " to sea before "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " could return to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the ship",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " with "
      },
      {
        "text": "her baby",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "The Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " aboard "
      },
      {
        "text": "the ship",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " were landed on "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and taken to the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mission San Gabriel",
        "entity_key": "mi_sg",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " where they soon died."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "It wasn't until 1853, some eighteen years later, that "
      },
      {
        "text": "Padre Gonzales",
        "entity_key": "jru",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara Mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "induced "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain George Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", an otter hunter, to attempt a trip to "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " in order to find "
      },
      {
        "text": "the lost woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " made three trips to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the wind-swept island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the last time taking "
      },
      {
        "text": "a group of Barbareno Indians",
        "entity_keys": [
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who combed "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " from one end to the other. After an arduous search a basket filled with feathers was uncovered. Searchers scattered the feathers but later found them all back in the basket and redoubled their efforts."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "It was "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " who came upon "
      },
      {
        "text": "the lost woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " as she was skinning a seal in front of three small huts made of whale ribs. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " showed no sign of being frightened and offered "
      },
      {
        "text": "her visitor",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "food. "
      },
      {
        "text": "By signs she indicated ",
        "tropes": [
          10,
          13,
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her baby",
        "tropes": [
          10,
          13,
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " had been killed years before. She told ",
        "tropes": [
          10,
          13,
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her rescuer",
        "tropes": [
          10,
          13,
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " how she had existed on sea food and seals killed with crude stone weapons, she showed them well-hidden caves and canyons where she hid when ",
        "tropes": [
          10,
          13,
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "marauding Russians and Aleuts",
        "tropes": [
          10,
          13,
          11
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "rfurcompany",
          "iba",
          "natam_aleuts"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " visited ",
        "tropes": [
          10,
          13,
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the lonely isle",
        "tropes": [
          10,
          13,
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " on foraging expeditions.",
        "tropes": [
          10,
          13,
          11
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Captain Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "his group",
        "entity_keys": [
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " returned with her to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " where she created a great deal of excitement. It is reported that the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara Mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " where "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " was staying, turned down a fabulous offer for her to join "
      },
      {
        "text": "a circus",
        "entity_key": "tru",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " side show and tour the world."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Food on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "was new to her, however, and the shock to her system after forty-five years of existing on sea food and seal meat soon caused her death."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Her dress of bird skins, her trinkets including woven grass bottles and wooden knives were sent to the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Vatican Museum",
        "entity_key": "mu_vaticanmuseum",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Rome",
        "entity_key": "ci_rom",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", although history recounts some were destroyed in the great "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Francisco",
        "entity_key": "ci_sf",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " fire of 1906."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Her death marked the passing of the last living Channel Island Indian. She was the sole survivor of ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a hardy race of peaceful seagoing Indians",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who had known a \"shangri-la\" for hundreds of years.",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "[...]"
      }
    ]
  ]
}